We live on a gravel road that is so heavily trafficked that it’s almost always in terrible condition but my taxes keep going up. There is no excuse for some of the roads around here to not be paved at the rate at which they are travelled. When local Economic Development invests in businesses outside of Mills County rather than local, active businesses but the local businesses taxes keep going up, that becomes a hard pill to swallow. Better roads, realistic taxes, better community amenities and more good paying jobs are what every community needs to prosper. Mills County is no different.
